Yesterday, Jennifer Klein, the Assistant to the President and Director of the Gender Policy Council, along with other senior officials, met with Dr. Cochav Elkayam-Levy, Chair of Israel's Civil Commission on October 7 Crimes by Hamas Against Women and Children. The Biden-Harris Administration has expressed deep concern over the reports of sexual violence used by Hamas against Israeli women and children during the October 7 attacks. Dr. Elkayam-Levy discussed her work in gathering testimony and evidence of the events and addressing gender-based violence committed by Hamas. The group emphasized the need to condemn sexual violence by Hamas and for international commitment to holding perpetrators accountable and supporting survivors. Director Klein reiterated the President's commitment to using all available resources to address sexual violence in conflict and to secure the release of women and girls held as hostages by Hamas.